Context:
* Better Jobs Ontario is an Ontario government-funded program for laid-off workers with skills training for jobs in growing fields.
* The information session is designed to guide applicants through the process and is open to domestic applicants (Canadian citizens or permanent residents).
* The duration of the session is approximately 1 hour and it's free of cost.
* Interested individuals can contact betterjobsontario@georgebrown.ca for more information.
* Attending the session is not required to apply, domestic students can see the application guide instead.
* Contact numbers for inquiries are 416-415-2000 and TTY: 1-877-515-5559. Email inquiry can be made to ask.george@georgebrown.ca.
* George Brown College's land acknowledgment can be learned more about.
* Individuals can sign up to receive application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, tours and more.
* The information contained in the website is subject to change without notice.
* Contact details for social media hub are also provided.
